This is a money making racket dressed up as green. 70% coniferous will do untold damage to biodiversity and native flora and fauna, it will make good profit though. Plant 90% deciduous and bring back natural forests and stop thinking profit first for our children's sake!

@RTERadio1 the great forest plan is nothing more than profiteering dress up as green. 70% coniferous that's the money, the rest is the sop. Conifers kill biodiversity and will not improve the chances of flora and fauna being supported. @ExtinctRebelsIE

Exactly. If land was preserved and managed for wildlife a mixed deciduous forest would self seed over time where other native flora and fauna could be facilitated by prudent management. Set aside land, protect it and just leave it alone. That's how we can restore #biodiversity.https://twitter.com/Irishwildlife/status/1167735380310994944 …

Thread: I trained as a natural scientist & focused on the conservation & history of Scottish, Manx & Irish landscapes, flora & fauna. I loved tracking pine martens & wild red deer, spotting kites & discovering orchids.    Nowadays I create an alternative fauna in my imagination pic.twitter.com/IatHAM2ZnS
